text.tspan: Create in me a pure heart, O God
Various Aspects of the Inner Life — Dealing with the Heart
Oh, purify my heart, Lord, wholly;
Empty all of my spirit utterly;
So pure in heart, I’d love Thee, supremely;
Poor in spirit, the kingdom I’d receive.
Unload everything from the depth of my being;
How blest to decrease, in spirit fully emptied,
To receive Thy vast riches bountif’lly!
Oh, purify our heart, Lord, wholly;
Empty all of our spirit utterly;
So pure in heart, we’d see You solely;
Poor in spirit, the kingdom we’d receive.
Lord, make us that people who’d give You the way
To bring Your kingdom to earth, we pray;
Your name sanctify; fulfill Your will divine;
Quickly come for Your glorious wedding day.
Lord, we’d be that people who’d give You the way
To bring Your kingdom to earth today,
Your name sanctify, fulfill Your will divine,
And hasten Your glorious wedding day.
